news.title: New home prices in China fall 0.5% month-on-month in October 2024
news.para: New home prices were down 0.5% month-on-month after a 0.7% dip in September, the slowest pace in seven months, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: Property investment in China falls 10.3% year-on-year in Jan-Oct 2024
news.para: Property sales by floor area in January-October fell 15.8% from a year earlier, versus a 17.1% drop in January-September.

news.title: Bihar cabinet approves Rs 115 crore for Patna Metro Rail project
news.para: A portion of these funds will be used by the Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) for track work, lift and escalator installations as well as the supply of train sets.

news.title: Bihar cabinet approves Rs 1 lakh aid for homeless families to buy land
news.para: This decision comes as district administrations are facing challenges in convincing private landowners to sell their land below market rates for use as homestead land for landless families.

news.title: Residents of Dwarka Dham colony file complaint against builder over power supply issues
news.para: The single power supply (HT connection) of the colony is issued in the name of the builder, as the society has not been handed over due to incomplete work. For the past five months, the power supply of the colony is being disconnected by the power distribution company for a day or two due to outstanding payment.

news.title: Goa TCP approves Inorbit Malls India's conversion of 23,497 sq meter of orchard land
news.para: The approvals give the green light for Inorbit Malls India, a subsidiary of K Raheja Corporation, to go ahead with the conversion of orchard land, which includes a heritage trail running through Panelim village adjacent to Old Goa.

news.title: Prestige Group acquires 22,135 sq meters land in Mira Bhayandar for Rs 291.58 crore
news.para: The acquired land will be planned for residential development spanning approximately one million sq ft of carpet area. The cost of acquisition is around Rs 291.58 crore.

news.title: Buildox fined for collecting flat booking amount without Telangana RERA approval
news.para: Complainant Sharath had alleged that the builder, Buildox Private Limited, was marketing and collecting funds for a project named ‘The Continent' at Kondapur/Hafeezpet without RERA registration.

news.title: Grasim Industries profit declines 45.6% to Rs 1,100 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 11.05 per cent to Rs 33,562.85 crore during the quarter under review from Rs 30,220.68 crore a year earlier.

news.title: Telangana RERA restrains Beccun Infrastructures from third-party interests in its project
news.para: This decision follows complaints filed by the Beccun Lifestyle Cultural Association representing over 200 flat buyers which alleged unauthorised construction and delays in completing the project.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders Pareena Infrastructure to hand over flats to buyers within 30 Days
news.para: "The respondent, Pareena Infrastructure Pvt Ltd, is directed to also execute the conveyance deed in favour of the complainants after settling the dues, if any, within 90 days from the date of this order," stated the Authority.

news.title: Sobha's net profit rises 74.56% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Sobha's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 965.29 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 24.77 per cent from Rs 773.64 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shriram Properties posts net loss of Rs 79 lakh in Q2 FY25
news.para: Shriram Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 155.10 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 32.93 per cent from Rs 231.24 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Omaxe's net loss widens to Rs 239.48 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Omaxe's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 398.32 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 47.62 per cent from Rs 269.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: ED invites defrauded Shine City investors to claim seized properties in Lucknow
news.para: He issued a proclamation inviting those victims with legitimate claims on Shine City Group properties to submit and establish their investments to validate their claims for property restoration.

news.title: Pune civic body likely to suffer property tax shortfall due to poll code
news.para: Property tax revenue is the highest source of incomefor Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC). The civic administration had set a target of Rs2,600 crore from this levy, which may fall short by around Rs300 crore.

news.title: House prices in UK rise at fastest pace in over two years: RICS
news.para: The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors said its house price balance rose to +16 from +11 in September, its highest level since September 2022, when the economic plans of former prime minister Liz Truss sent mortgage markets into a spin.

news.title: House prices in New Zealand rise 1% in October 2024: REINZ report
news.para: Seasonally adjusted median house prices rose 1% in October from the previous month, and by 0.7% on the same time last year, data from REINZ showed.

news.title: Goa: HC grants temporary relief to occupants of illegal structures on government land in Cunchelim
news.para: The court did not stay the demolition but recorded their undertaking that they would vacate their structures in six weeks.
